commitResults.messageBody:
Existing code uses Person to represent an entry.

This is inconsistent with the theme of the project, which uses Project
to represent an single entry.

Let's replace all instances of Person to Project.

Project currently takes in address as a parameter for each project.

This is not relevant to the project at this stage.

Let's remove the address model.

Project currently takes in email as a parameter for each project.

This is not relevant to the theme of the project at this stage.

Let's remove the email model.

Project currently takes in phone number as a parameter for each project.

This is not relevant to the theme of the project at this stage.

Let's remove the phone model.

Find command does a simple search to check whether the name fully
matches the name of a project in the project book.

This limits the flexibility that the user has when conducting searches.

Let's:
 * Upgrade the find command to allow for partial name matches
 * Allow users to specify whether any or all keywords need to match
 before an entry is returned
 * Implement support for predicate chaining in anticipation for more
 complicated searches in the future

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement find by description and tag
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command is currently limited to searching for projects based on
name only.

This limits the flexibility that the user has when conducting searches.

Let's:
 * Upgrade the find command to allow for partial description matches
 * Upgrade the find command to allow for full tag matches
